Description: Terracotta figure wing fragment from a Eros or Nike figurine. Mould-made and solid, originally added to the back of a hollow figure, now lost. Well preserved traces of white coating. Fine, dense red-brown clay fabric with yellow surfaces and some dark red (grog?) inclusions.
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.

Parallels from of c. 200BC-100BC Myrina, Hellenistic wing attachments to Eros and Nike figures (Louvre, Paris Ly1651; Bo 158; Myr 171; Myr 86; Myr 54). Numbered May 1985 so prov. not certain, but with Nauk. objects. Drilled for analysis or display?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (DB.370) (Phase 3)
